        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>April 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Bowman</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I send by Railway today the book which you lent me.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I could not help looking through many parts; &amp; my wonder is that any us have eyes in our heads, seeing what a frightful number of horrid diseases the eye is liable to.</p>
<p>Many thanks | Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8280.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to William Bowman, 8 April [1872]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Bowman lent CD <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5057.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Soelberg Wells’s</ref> <hi rend="italic">A treatise on the diseases of the eye</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8278.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Wells 1869</ref>; see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8266.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from F. C. Donders, 1 April 1872</ref> and n. 3).</note>
